5 A BILL
6 TO BE ENTITLED
7 AN ACT
8
9 Relating to public high schools; to require high
10 schools to excuse students from class to participate in
11 National Signing Day activities related to the acceptance of
12 athletic scholarships, postsecondary school educational
13 commitments, apprenticeship programs, and military
14 enlistments; and to provide reasonable accommodations for
15 those activities.
16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
17 Section 1. (a) High school students who sign commitment
18 letters at a ceremony during instructional time at school as
19 part of organized National Signing Day activities related to
20 the acceptance of athletic scholarships, postsecondary school
21 educational commitments, commitments to apprenticeship
22 programs, and military enlistments shall be excused from
23 class.
24 (b) For activities conducted pursuant to subsection
25 (a):
26 (1) A school shall provide reasonable accommodations.
27 For purposes of this subdivision, reasonable accommodations
28 shall include, but not be limited to, meeting space with
Page 1

shall include, but not be limited to, meeting space with
HB75 Engrossed
29 Internet connectivity access and seating, the use of which
30 will not interfere with instruction;
31 (2) Guests may attend subject to local board of
32 education policy; and
33 (3) A school principal may excuse other students to
34 attend.
35 Section 2. This act shall become effective on October
36 1, 2026.
